message: optimize deduping initialization benchmarking barebones rail application seeing lot lock contention looked thread spending lot time waiting grab mutex dedupmap inside  happened activesupport defined somevar somevar lot filling output template thus thread spending lot time method fighting dedup string  fix instead deduping accessed let dedup defined message initially populated inside definedmessages map way get effect dedup  fix considerable effect single thread performance ruby require benchmark class test def initialize foo foo end def defined_test defined foo foo end end test.new benchmark.ips benchmark benchmark.time  defined t.defined_test  end  fix  warming defined 256.296k 100ms calculating defined 11.992m 4.4 239.380m 20.008996s  without fix  warming defined 224.042k 100ms calculating defined 7.373m 2.5 147.420m 20.009003s  ... even noticeable effect multi threaded performance ruby def defined_loop count foo true count.times defined foo foo end end defined_loop put warmup done start time.now .map thread.new defined_loop end end t.each join put done time.now start second  case able find decent ruby multithreaded benchmark harness pardon crappiness ran fine time got linux dual core skylake fix  done 12.442 second done 12.284 second done 12.803 second done 13.724 second done 13.844 second  visualvm look like thread state graph fix http i.imgur.com i3f72h4.png without fix  done 71.088 second done 71.664 second done 64.57 second done 65.504 second done 62.81 second  visualvm look like thread state graph without fix http i.imgur.com 0ulo9zm.png expected major win multithreaded scenario
